! Overview

`rimir/msg-import` turns dropped Outlook `.msg` files into clean markdown tiddlers with YAML frontmatter. It is a configuration-only plugin: no server JS modules of its own, no widgets — all the heavy lifting is done by plugins that were already in the wiki:

* ''rimir/file-upload'' handles the drop, content-hash dedup, and stores the binary under `files/email/`.
* ''rimir/file-pipeline'' auto-runs the bundled pipeline when the MIME type is `application/vnd.ms-outlook`.
* ''rimir/runner'' executes the Python extractor as a whitelisted command from `runner-actions.json`.
* ''rimir/frontmatter'' deserializes the resulting `.md` body back into tiddler fields on save / reload.

!! What you get per drop

For a dropped `meeting.msg`, three tiddler groups appear:

* `meeting.msg` — the original binary, served via `_canonical_uri`
* `meeting.msg.email` — the markdown body, `type: text/x-frontmattered-markdown`, with all email metadata in YAML frontmatter
* `meeting.msg.attachments/<filename>` — one artifact tiddler per non-inline attachment

Inline images (`cid:` refs in HTML body) are saved as static files under `files/email/_derived/<basename>/cid_<id>.<ext>` and the body's image refs are rewritten to point at them.

!! Pipeline shape

```json
{
  "name": "msg",
  "match": ["application/vnd.ms-outlook"],
  "steps": [
    { "id": "convert",     "action": "convert-msg-body",       "captureStdout": true,  ... },
    { "id": "attachments", "action": "extract-msg-attachments","scanDir": true,       ... },
    { "id": "summary",     "type": "llm", "condition": { "config": "$:/config/rimir/msg-import/llm-summary", "equals": "yes" }, ... }
  ]
}
```

The LLM summary step is gated by config and is off by default.
